    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review behaviour in schools legislation and guidance ",
        "additional_details": "The review should look at rethinking \"misbehaviour\" definitions to help prevent harsh punishments for minor infractions, fostering a healthier environment that is focused on learning and not rules. A review could provide an opportunity to look at how to create a fairer disciplinary system, benefiting students' well-being. A post-pandemic education system requires empathy. Advocating for this review is vital for a just and nurturing educational system. The review should also look at the benefits of adopting the approach by Wales of giving 24 hours\u2019 notice for after-school detentions to help promote transparency and minimise safety risks.",
        "background": "The Government should review how behaviour is managed, including looking at the Education & Inspections Act 2006 and its behaviour in schools\u2019 guidance. ",
